---
mode: prompt
bind_model: anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
params:
  topic: string
  count: number = 3
---
// H9a acceptance area (d) — a params loom forcing a real binder pass.
// Two `params:` fields (one defaulted) route to the binder (NOT a bypass), so a
// genuine binder pass over the declared params runs before the body. DECISION
// (production conformance): the binder runs OFF-session and INVISIBLE — its
// three-arm envelope JSON is NEVER streamed to the user / stdout. On a
// successful bind the observable proof is the `bind_echo` success note
// (`Running /acc-params-binder: …`). The `bind_model:` is provider-qualified
// (`anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5`) because the bare id can be ambiguous across
// configured providers; a non-bypass loom with no resolvable binder model fails
// to load. The body is a pure-literal `respond`.
respond "ok"
